{
  "texts": [
    "The augmented EnKF makes the strong assumption that the parameters and observations follow a linear Gaussian structure.",
    "An alternative approach for dealing with the static parameters is to marginalise out the hidden states in a sequential fashion.",
    "Recall the factorisation of π t (θ|y 0:t) in (5) and the assumption of a weighted sample of size M, {θ 1:M, u 1:M t-1 }, from π t-1 (θ|y 0:t-1).",
    "Upon receipt of y t, and in the context of time-varying parameters, Katzfuss et al. (2019) (see also Frei and Künsch, 2011, among others) propose to use the observed-data likelihood under the EnKF to reweight parameter particles.",
    "We adapt the resulting particle ensemble Kalman filter (PEnKF) to our problem as follows."
  ]
}